Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.48,0:00:05.82,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to muster the last of \Nyour strength, use it to leave here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.82,0:00:06.98,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.98,0:00:10.12,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Any human who loses this \Nmuch blood is gonna die!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.12,0:00:12.40,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point in getting \Nout if she's dead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:15.69,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,Rachel Gardner is still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.58,0:00:19.13,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,If you get out right now, you can save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.13,0:00:20.83,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:22.96,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,Go, and you will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.34,0:00:25.42,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,Now, go quickly, Zack!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.63,0:00:27.38,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.36,0:02:20.60,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,Zack...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.34,0:02:23.58,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,Zack!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.19,0:02:39.20,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,Who could have guessed that \Nit would end this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.40,0:02:42.58,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.14,0:02:44.65,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.65,0:02:46.60,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,I admit that I was self-serving.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.18,0:02:50.44,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right. Even though \NI was working for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.62,0:02:54.40,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,But I... Nothing I did was wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.74,0:02:56.53,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,What I did for my own happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.53,0:03:00.19,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,and to stop anyone who violated \Nthe rules of this building,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.19,0:03:02.41,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,should have been beneficial to you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.09,0:03:07.93,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,It is true that I got to see something \Nof profound interest, thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.32,0:03:13.31,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,I believed Zack was a being \Nthat possessed invisible wings,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.70,0:03:18.55,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,but now those wings have become\N entirely imperceptible to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.55,0:03:20.19,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,Invisible wings?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.57,0:03:23.97,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,Did you actually think he was an angel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.93,0:03:27.05,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.05,0:03:31.39,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,Precisely because he was so pure that he \Nthought of only one thing: killing people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.04,0:03:37.54,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,But then Zack learned to wield his \Nblade for someone else's benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.54,0:03:40.64,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,As a result of this, his blade broke,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.64,0:03:43.03,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,and he fell from the ranks \Nof angels, becoming a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.58,0:03:47.58,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,No, perhaps it is more accurate \Nto say he was always human.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.97,0:03:51.15,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, the one who showed this to me
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.15,0:03:55.80,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,was Rachel Gardner, the one \NI had denounced as a witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.80,0:03:59.80,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,It was a transformation \Nboth dizzying and striking,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.32,0:04:05.46,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,for a girl who was once so self-serving \Nand rife with contradiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.30,0:04:13.33,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,Looking back now, I see that the one who \Ntried to take Zack's humanity from him was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.33,0:04:16.15,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,Then why... why did you shoot me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.40,0:04:22.41,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,It was my own vain attempt at \Natoning for what I've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.59,0:04:27.28,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,My observation and \Nexperimentation are over now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.66,0:04:31.40,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,as is my duty to stand \Nin the position of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.05,0:04:34.46,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,After all this, what are you..
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.46,0:04:38.12,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,You brought that girl to this place,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.66,0:04:43.72,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,but although you were meant to steal \Nher soul, you sought to give her one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.22,0:04:48.76,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,You tried to become her God, did you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.15,0:04:53.49,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,But, Danny, you are no God.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.49,0:04:55.92,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,You must have known that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.92,0:04:59.47,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,But if I hadn't done that, I'd have nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.58,0:05:05.49,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,When I first looked into Rachel's eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.67,0:05:08.36,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,they were the eyes of \Nsomeone who'd lost all hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.05,0:05:11.49,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,...and would never love anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.88,0:05:16.46,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to give my love \Nto those eyes for eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.21,0:05:19.38,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,She gave new meaning...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.57,0:05:21.88,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,...to the life I thought I had lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.08,0:05:24.57,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,That gave me the power to do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.50,0:05:28.84,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't love her eyes any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.70,0:05:32.35,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,If she isn't all alone anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.66,0:05:36.21,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,there's no one left who'll accept \Nthe ugly thing that I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.69,0:05:41.33,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,By continuing to offer her your love, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.33,0:05:45.03,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,you hoped that she would \None day love you in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.02,0:05:52.20,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,Danny, both you and I are \Nmere humans, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.17,0:05:55.25,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... human?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.44,0:05:59.92,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,There was never anyone\Nhere who wasn't human.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.47,0:06:05.26,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,It is humans who create God, \Nas well as angels and people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.62,0:06:10.47,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,That may have been true for \NRachel Gardner, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.63,0:06:14.35,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,And the ones who attack\N and destroy all that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.80,0:06:16.64,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,...are those same people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.82,0:06:18.17,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.17,0:06:21.75,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,What have you seen in the \Npeople you've known here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.15,0:06:23.72,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.72,0:06:27.58,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, very little \Nhas significantly changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.95,0:06:32.16,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,They were ugly, blind in \Ntheir devotion, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.33,0:06:35.12,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,...so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.00,0:06:37.46,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.68,0:06:43.59,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,And Danny, I feel the same is true of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.81,0:06:47.53,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,You have been here longer than any other,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.53,0:06:49.74,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,yet I didn't realize it until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.74,0:06:50.55,main,Gray,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.28,0:06:56.19,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,It's already the end for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.19,0:07:00.56,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,Hearing you say I'm beautiful \Ndoesn't help much now, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.59,0:07:14.58,main,Danny,0000,0000,0000,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.64,0:07:26.20,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there. We're almost outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.98,0:07:28.96,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you die on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.12,0:07:50.94,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. We're outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.55,0:07:57.00,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,He said I could save you once we got out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.00,0:07:59.06,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,What did he mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.58,0:08:01.62,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,What am I supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.62,0:08:04.83,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Wake up! Come on, Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.14,0:08:06.57,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.58,0:08:12.10,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,I'm begging you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.10,0:08:13.76,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Open your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.09,0:08:15.18,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.28,0:08:27.11,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,That priest... This is what \Nhe meant by saving her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.96,0:08:33.78,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You there! Release the girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.24,0:08:36.20,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bother resisting!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:41.03,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Release the girl, put your hands behind \Nyour head, and get on your knees!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.93,0:08:47.92,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Ray, don't forget. I promised you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.26,0:08:51.63,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,...that I would kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.39,0:10:24.72,italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,The girl recovered from the burning building
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.32,0:10:30.00,italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,was found to be Rachel Gardner, the daughter \Nof the murdered Mr. and Mrs. Gardner,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.00,0:10:32.59,italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,who went missing while their \Ncase was being investigated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.59,0:10:36.25,italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,Isaac Foster, the man arrested on \Nsuspicion of blowing up the building,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.25,0:10:39.70,italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,is believed to be behind several past crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.70,0:10:42.57,sign_15338_104_Has_Isaac_Foster,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Has Isaac Foster confessed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.72,0:10:45.43,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He's not the one who blew up the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.99,0:10:49.35,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He's also denied kidnapping \Nthe girl who was with him
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.35,0:10:52.50,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,as well as killing her parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.50,0:10:55.00,sign_15338_104_Has_Isaac_Foster,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Has he also denied involvement in other crimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.18,0:10:58.67,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, he admitted guilt to \Nthose with shocking honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.42,0:11:02.60,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,"I don't lie," he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.80,0:11:05.39,sign_15338_104_Has_Isaac_Foster,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you can believe him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.60,0:11:08.68,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I don't think he's lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.14,0:11:09.88,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.50,0:11:14.79,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, that's a dumb idea. Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.79,0:11:18.09,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He's a twisted killer. No doubt about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.11,0:11:21.74,sign_15338_104_Has_Isaac_Foster,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Have you found out how he's connected to the girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.75,0:11:25.34,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The only answer he gives us \Nabout her is, "I don't know."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.23,0:11:31.21,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,\Nhe actually asked us about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.64,0:11:34.23,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He asked if she was alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.65,0:11:39.17,italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,So we told him she was,\N but all he said was, "Okay."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.67,0:11:42.05,sign_15338_104_Has_Isaac_Foster,Text,0000,0000,0000,,What was your first impression of Rachel Gardner?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.92,0:11:47.80,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,I thought she was a beautiful girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.24,0:11:50.84,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Her expression was very desolate, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.70,0:11:53.69,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I can't blame her for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.69,0:11:57.61,sign_15338_104_Has_Isaac_Foster,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Has she told you anything pertaining to this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.96,0:12:01.19,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,No, I've asked, but she denies \Nknowledge of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.19,0:12:03.95,sign_15338_104_Has_Isaac_Foster,Text,0000,0000,0000,,What sort of counseling are you giving her?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.17,0:12:07.62,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,My top priority is to help \Nher regain her peace of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.36,0:12:11.26,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,She gives very little in \Nthe way of facial cues,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.26,0:12:14.53,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,and she seems incapable of \Nexpressing her emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.37,0:12:19.59,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,And... all she wants to know \Nabout is that murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.59,0:12:23.43,sign_15338_104_Has_Isaac_Foster,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that she can't get\N the murderer out of her mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.64,0:12:25.05,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,I do think that's the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.24,0:12:30.18,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I've made an effort to keep \Nall information about him away from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.59,0:12:33.77,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,I've cut her off from the \Nthings that she fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.77,0:12:37.06,sign_15338_104_Has_Isaac_Foster,Text,0000,0000,0000,,I hope she'll make a speedy recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.11,0:12:40.20,italics,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,I'll keep working with her emotions, \Npatiently and persistently.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.37,0:14:30.55,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Rachel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:36.95,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Did you sleep well?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.67,0:14:41.48,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.12,0:14:45.42,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Your counseling for today \Nwill be in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.17,0:14:48.92,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,It's a gorgeous day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.41,0:14:55.48,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,After breakfast, why don't \Nwe take a nice walk outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.54,0:15:02.38,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.94,0:15:19.64,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Places like this are so relaxing, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.24,0:15:21.96,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.27,0:15:28.22,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Rachel, could you wait here for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.58,0:15:55.68,italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,The suspect in these serial \Nmurders and kidnappings,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.68,0:15:57.47,italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,Isaac Foster...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.33,0:16:12.15,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Has anything made you feel uneasy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.94,0:16:14.61,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.95,0:16:17.37,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Then have you been sleeping well?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.63,0:16:19.34,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.00,0:16:21.04,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.04,0:16:23.69,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call it a day, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.10,0:16:26.64,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry we started so late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.64,0:16:30.17,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,My session with another patient ran long.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.15,0:16:32.82,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,I'll walk you to your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.81,0:16:35.26,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,I can go by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.45,0:16:37.74,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let you do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.74,0:16:38.97,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.55,0:16:43.75,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,My, the sky looks so pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.20,0:16:46.84,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,It's a beautiful night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.00,0:16:49.56,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,A beautiful night?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.31,0:16:51.23,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.23,0:16:53.99,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,The best thing to do on a night like \Nthis is get into bed and sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.55,0:16:56.34,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have sweet dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.03,0:17:06.29,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Come, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.63,0:17:12.21,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Rachel, could it be that you're afraid?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.06,0:17:16.18,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotten much better\Nsince you came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.33,0:17:19.35,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,You're nothing like who you were
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.78,0:17:23.28,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,when you kept asking about \Nthat murderer you were with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.57,0:17:29.26,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,So... to put you at ease, I'll tell you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.26,0:17:31.32,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not supposed to, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.51,0:17:33.86,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,That murderer...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.42,0:17:39.78,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,...was sentenced to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.06,0:17:44.54,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,He... was?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.21,0:17:47.91,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'm sure you're surprised,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.91,0:17:50.58,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,but I believe this will \Nhelp you sleep in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.21,0:17:51.71,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.98,0:17:54.54,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.44,0:18:04.33,main,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Go straight to bed and sleep, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.35,0:18:11.32,italics,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,The truth was that I hadn't \Nslept well the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.95,0:18:14.57,italics,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,I just couldn't calm myself down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.80,0:18:18.07,italics,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,I was sure I wouldn't \Nsleep that night, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.56,0:18:24.16,italics,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,But... there was nothing left \Nto do but close my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.20,0:18:49.31,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.31,0:18:53.17,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,There's that boring look on your face again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.17,0:18:55.61,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,Zack... How...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.61,0:18:57.90,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? How what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.39,0:19:00.99,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, weren't you in prison?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.99,0:19:03.74,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well... obviously, I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.79,0:19:05.64,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.53,0:19:08.88,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,That day...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.88,0:19:12.71,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,I told you I'd carry our promise with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.88,0:19:14.79,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, so what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.79,0:19:17.92,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Who said you could go and \Ntake it for yourself, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.55,0:19:19.48,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.80,0:19:25.31,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,You still... want to kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.48,0:19:30.83,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,You know me. When I want something, \NI don't let it get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.83,0:19:32.48,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,So hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.48,0:19:35.23,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.71,0:19:38.69,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,Or did you already forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.99,0:19:43.31,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,No, Zack. I didn't forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.08,0:19:45.93,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,I could never forget!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.52,0:19:50.38,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,After all, we promised!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.94,0:19:55.04,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,You and I promised each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.22,0:19:57.42,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! So come on, Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.42,0:19:58.13,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.18,0:20:05.35,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Zack...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.22,0:20:07.34,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.79,0:20:09.91,main,Rachel,0000,0000,0000,,...kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.38,0:20:16.31,main,Zack,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what you want, \Nstop crying and smile.
